An immersive and interactive experience
Aug 2024 â€¢ Family
Location: A short walk from either a tram or metro station, making it easily accessible.

Entry:
It's best to pre-book tickets, either through special offers or directly from the museum's website.

Experience:
Allocate around 2 hours to fully explore and enjoy the museum.
Suitable for visitors of all ages, and visiting with a group adds to the fun.
Staff members are available to explain the meaning behind the artwork, enhancing your understanding of the exhibits.

Photo Opportunities:
Tons of photo-worthy moments, so ensure your phone has enough storage!
The museum features several photo booths for additional prints, available for purchase after the visit.

Facilities:
The museum is well-maintained, with cleanliness and clear signage.
A cafÃ© is conveniently located near the exit, perfect for relaxing after a busy photo session.

Tips:
Visit during off-peak hours to avoid long queues and fewer people in your photos.
It's a good idea to check the waiting time, as it may vary depending on the day and time.
